    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output="Based on the provided excerpts from SpaceX's financial statements and prospectus notes, here is a detailed breakdown of the Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock conversion rates and their adjustment for the 2026 Stock Split.\n\n### 1. Standard Conversion Rate for SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock\n*   **Post-2026 Stock Split:** Each share of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock is convertible into **50 shares of SpaceX Common Stock**. This is the explicit, fixed conversion ratio stated in the documents following the split.\n*   **Pre-2026 Stock Split:** The conversion rate was based on a formula: *Initial Price of the Series ÷ Conversion Price*. The exact pre-split rate is not explicitly calculated in the provided text, but it was subject to adjustment for anti-dilution events.\n\n### 2. Adjustment for the 2026 Stock Split\n*   **Nature of the Split:** On May 4, 2026, SpaceX effected a **five-for-one (5:1) forward stock split** for its Class A, B, and C Common Stock.\n*   **Adjustment Mechanism:** The conversion rate for the Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was **proportionately adjusted** to account for this split.\n*   **Result:** The adjustment resulted in the fixed post-split conversion ratio of **50:1**. This implies that the pre-split conversion rate would have been **10 shares of Common Stock per share of Preferred Stock** (since 10 shares × 5 = 50 shares).\n\n### 3. Impact on Related Equity Instruments\nThe 2026 Stock Split retroactively affected all share and per-share information. Consequently:\n*   **All historical share counts** (e.g., in financial statements) have been adjusted as if the 5:1 split had occurred at the beginning of the earliest period presented.\n*   **Merger Conversion Ratios (pre-2026 basis):** The conversion ratios for xAI equity awards into SpaceX stock, which occurred in February 2026, are stated on a **pre-split basis**. These figures would be multiplied by 5 to reflect the post-split reality.\n    *   **xAI Options/RSUs/RSAs:** Converted at **0.1433 shares** of SpaceX Common Stock per xAI award.\n    *   **X RSUs:** Converted to xAI RSUs at a rate of **2.776 shares** of xAI stock per X RSU.\n\n### 4. Key Series-Specific Details (as of March 31, 2026)\nThe tables provide the financial terms for each series, which are the basis for the conversion formula.\n\n| Series | Initial Price Per Share | Dividend Per Share | Implied Post-Split Common Stock Value* |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **Series G** | $77.46 | $3.87 | $1.5492 |\n| **Series H** | $135.00 | $6.75 | $2.7000 |\n| **Series I** | $169.00 | $8.45 | $3.3800 |\n| **Series J** | $186.00 | $9.30 | $3.7200 |\n| **Series K** | $204.00 | $10.20 | $4.0800 |\n| **Series L** | $214.00 | $10.70 | $4.2800 |\n| **Series M** | $220.00 | $11.00 | $4.4000 |\n| **Series N** | $270.00 | $13.50 | $5.4000 |\n\n*\\*Implied Value = Initial Price / 50 (post-split conversion ratio). This represents the theoretical value of the common stock received upon conversion.*\n\n### 5. Other Affected Terms\n*   **Automatic Conversion:** The Preferred Stock automatically converts upon a **Qualified IPO** or a date specified by the board.\n*   **Liquidation Preference:** Holders receive the greater of their liquidation preference (initial price + unpaid dividends) or the amount they would get if converted to Common Stock immediately prior to a liquidation event.\n*   **Pro Forma Financials:** All pro forma per-share data (like EPS) assumes the **Preferred Conversion** (all preferred stock converting to common) and the **Class C Reclassification** occurred as of January 1, 2025, with share counts adjusted for the 2026 Stock Split.\n\n**In summary:** The 5:1 stock split multiplied all share counts and dividends by 5 and divided all per-share prices by 5. This adjustment was baked into the charter, setting a new fixed conversion rate of **50 common shares for each preferred share**, retroactively applied to all financial reporting periods. For specific exercise prices of options and RSU terms post-merger, you would need to apply this 5x multiplier to the pre-split figures provided (e.g., the xAI option exercise price was divided by 0.1433 on a pre-split basis). For full details, the documents consistently reference **Note 12 - Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock and Shareholders' Equity**.",
