    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='Based on the provided S-1 prospectus excerpts, here is a comprehensive summary of all information regarding stock options, RSUs, ESPPs, equity compensation plans, exercise prices, share-based compensation, and relevant split adjustments.\n\n### **1. Equity Compensation Plans**\nThe term **"Equity Plans"** collectively refers to:\n*   **SpaceX Plans:**\n    *   **A&R 2024 Plan:** The Amended and Restated 2024 Equity Incentive Plan.\n    *   **A&R 2017 ESPP:** The Amended and Restated 2017 Employee Stock Purchase Plan.\n    *   **2015 Plan**\n    *   **2012 Equity Incentive Plan**\n*   **Assumed xAI Plans:**\n    *   xAI’s 2023 Equity Incentive Plan, 2023 Incentive Plan, and 2025 Equity Incentive Plan.\n\n**Key Plan Mechanics (A&R 2024 Plan):**\n*   **Shares:** Shares subject to expired, terminated, forfeited awards, or shares withheld for taxes/exercise prices are returned to the share reserve.\n*   **Eligibility:** Current/prospective employees, non-employee directors, and consultants of SpaceX and its affiliates.\n*   **Administration:** By a "Plan Administrator" (typically the Board or a committee).\n\n### **2. Award Types & Terms**\n#### **Stock Options (A&R 2024 Plan & CEO Award)**\n*   **Types:** Incentive Stock Options (ISOs) and Nonstatutory Stock Options (NSOs).\n*   **Term:** Generally not to exceed **10 years** (or 5 years for ISOs granted to 10%+ shareholders).\n*   **Exercise Price:**\n    *   Generally **not less than fair market value (FMV) on the grant date** (or 110% of FMV for ISOs to 10%+ shareholders).\n    *   Payment methods: Cash, broker-assisted sale, previously owned shares, or withholding of shares.\n*   **Vesting Schedules (Typical):**\n    *   4-year vesting with 25% cliff after one year, then monthly.\n    *   6-year vesting with 20% cliff after two years, then monthly.\n*   **Specific Grants (2025 Fiscal Year):**\n    *   **Gwynne Shotwell:** Options to purchase 324,325 shares @ $37.00 (5/10/25) and 3,537,740 shares @ $42.40 (10/20/25).\n    *   **Bret Johnsen:** Options to purchase 324,325 shares @ $37.00 (5/10/25) and 141,510 shares @ $42.40 (10/20/25).\n*   **CEO Performance-Based Options (xAI Award - Terminated):**\n    *   Granted to Elon Musk in Nov 2025, subject to market, performance, and service conditions.\n    *   **Grant Date Fair Value:** $2,205 million. Terminated in March 2026.\n\n#### **Restricted Stock Units (RSUs)**\n*   **General Terms:** Right to receive shares upon vesting. Restrictions/conditions set by Plan Administrator, may include performance conditions.\n*   **Vesting Schedules (Typical):**\n    *   25% after year 1, then quarterly for 4 years.\n    *   12.5% after 6 months, then quarterly for 4 years.\n    *   20% after year 1, then semi-annually for 5 years.\n*   **Valuation & Financials:**\n    *   **Weighted-Avg. Grant Date Fair Value (2025):** $54.84 per share.\n    *   **Total Fair Value of RSUs Released (2025):** $2,151 million.\n*   **Specific Grants (2025):**\n    *   **Gwynne Shotwell:** 19,650 RSUs (in lieu of salary) and 27,030 RSUs, both granted 5/10/25.\n    *   **X Employees:** Performance-based RSUs granted in 2023 were modified in 2025 to remove performance conditions.\n\n#### **Restricted Stock Awards (RSAs)**\n*   **Terms:** Shares transferred subject to forfeiture risk. **Weighted-Avg. Grant Date Fair Value (2025):** $93.87 per share.\n*   **CEO Award (SpaceX CEO Award):**\n    *   **1 billion Class B shares** granted to Elon Musk in Jan 2026.\n    *   **Vesting Conditions:** Performance-based tied to:\n        1.  Market cap milestones in 15 tranches ($500B to $7.5T).\n        2.  Establishment of a permanent human colony on Mars with ≥1 million inhabitants.\n    *   **Grant Date Fair Value:** $90.40 to $95.92 per share.\n\n#### **Employee Stock Purchase Plans (ESPPs)**\n*   **A&R 2017 ESPP:**\n    *   **Discount:** Purchase price is **not less than 85% of the lower of the FMV on the offering date or purchase date**.\n    *   **Terms:** Adjustments for corporate actions (splits, dividends). Non-transferable.\n*   **NQ ESPP (2023):** Allowed purchase at FMV (no discount). **Cancelled in April 2026.**\n*   **Share Activity (2025):**\n    *   **ESPP:** 6.3 million shares issued.\n    *   **NQ ESPP:** 0.2 million shares issued.\n*   **Remaining Shares (12/31/2025):**\n    *   **ESPP:** 27.0 million shares available.\n    *   **NQ ESPP:** 4.8 million shares available.\n\n### **3. Share Counts & Reserves (as of 12/31/2025 or 3/31/2026)**\n*   **Outstanding Awards:** The tables exclude awards subject to unmet performance/market conditions (e.g., 14.5 million as of 12/31/2025).\n*   **Shares Reserved for Future Grants:**\n    *   **Under All Plans:** 543.8 million shares available for future grant.\n*   **ESPP Shares:** 27.0 million (ESPP) + 4.8 million (NQ ESPP) shares available.\n*   **Preamble Exclusions (for offering share count):** Shares issuable upon exercise of options, vesting of RSUs, and reserves under the A&R 2024 Plan and A&R 2017 ESPP are excluded.\n\n### **4. Financial Impact & Fair Value**\n*   **Valuation Methods:**\n    *   **Standard Options/RSUs:** Black-Scholes model (options) or grant-date FMV (RSUs/RSAs).\n    *   **CEO Awards (Complex):** **Monte Carlo simulation** model.\n*   **Expense Recognition:**\n    *   **Service-only awards:** Straight-line over vesting period.\n    *   **Performance awards:** Graded vesting basis; recognized when vesting becomes probable.\n*   **Key Financial Figures (2025):**\n    *   **Total Remaining Share-Based Compensation Expense:** $4,842 million (to be recognized over avg. 3.2 years).\n    *   **Total Intrinsic Value of Options Exercised:** $1,249 million.\n    *   **Total Fair Value of RSUs Released:** $2,151 million.\n\n### **5. Critical Adjustments: Stock Splits & Conversions**\n*   **2026 Stock Split:** All historical share counts and exercise prices in the filing are adjusted to reflect this split. References to "pre-2026 Stock Split basis" indicate original, unsplit terms.\n*   **xAI Merger Conversion (0.1433 Ratio):**\n    *   **Options:** Each xAI option became a SpaceX option for **0.1433 shares**. Exercise price divided by 0.1433.\n    *   **Vested RSUs:** Each converted to right to receive 0.1433 SpaceX shares.\n    *   **Unvested RSUs:** Each converted to 0.1433 of a SpaceX RSU.\n    *   **RSAs:** Each converted to 0.1433 SpaceX RSAs.\n    *   **Cash Alternative:** Holders of vested xAI options/RSUs could elect $75.46 cash per share.\n*   **X Merger Conversion:** Each X RSU was converted to a xAI RSU to receive 2.776 shares.\n*   **Class Conversion:** Awards in Class C common stock convert 1:1 to Class A common stock as part of the Class C Reclassification.\n\n### **6. Outstanding Awards at Fiscal Year-End (12/31/2025)**\n*   No NEOs held outstanding RSUs or unvested stock awards.\n*   Outstanding stock options for NEOs are detailed in the table above, all exercisable for Class C stock (convertible to Class A).\n\n### **Summary of Key Exercise Prices Referenced**\n*   **Specific Grants:** $19.40, $37.00, $42.40 (all post-split, for Class C options).\n*   **Fair Value Floor:** Exercise price cannot be less than FMV on grant date (with specific exceptions for ISOs).\n*   **xAI Award Valuation Milestones:** $213 billion to $1,313 billion (market conditions).',
